<p><b>Information Cards</b> are personal digital identities that people can use online. Visually, each Information Card has a card-shaped picture and a card name associated with it that enable people to organize their digital identities and to easily select one they want to use for any given interaction. The Information Card metaphor is implemented by Identity Selectors like <a href="/wiki/Windows_CardSpace" title="Windows CardSpace">Windows CardSpace</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=DigitalMe&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="DigitalMe (page does not exist)">DigitalMe</a> or <a href="/wiki/Higgins_project" title="Higgins project">Higgins Identity Selector</a>.</p>
